 fraction of oxygen in the O VI ionization stage is 0.2, we obtain Omega_b(O\nVI) > 0.004/h_75. This is comparable to the combined cosmological mass density\nof stars and cool gas in galaxies and X-ray emitting gas in galaxy clusters at\nlow redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Mar 2000 09:50:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
